{
  "message": "fix(shellcheck): correct SC2078 \u2014 move is_machine_format call outside [[ ]]\n\nShellCheck SC2078: inside `[[ cond && ! is_machine_format ]]`, the\nfunction name is treated as a constant non-empty string, so\n`! is_machine_format` is always false. The intent was to invoke the\nfunction and negate its exit status. Moved the call outside the\n`[[ ... ]]` block so it runs as a normal command with its exit code\nevaluated by `!`.\n\nPre-existing issue from commit aa9fb87 (2025-11-16), but fixing it as\npart of the #41/#42 CI cleanup. The ubs-ruby module's `maybe_clear`\nhelper would previously have never cleared the screen even when\ninteractive and not in CI/machine-format mode.\n\n(Remaining shellcheck errors in other modules \u2014 SC2259\nheredoc-overrides-pipe \u2014 are larger structural bugs in pre-existing\ncode that need domain knowledge of the helper-script architecture to\nfix safely; leaving those for a separate PR.)",
